=beginObject#freeze(from ~/.rdoc)------------------------------------------------------------------------------  obj.freeze    -> obj------------------------------------------------------------------------------Prevents further modifications to obj. A RuntimeError will beraised if modification is attempted. There is no way to unfreeze a frozenobject. See alsoObject#frozen?.This method returns self.  a = [ "a", "b", "c" ]  a.freeze  a << "z"produces:  prog.rb:3:in `<<': can't modify frozen array (RuntimeError)   from prog.rb:3=end